<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> *<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFVarniEd._Prof._Sagarmal_Jain.2C_Translated_Justice_T.K._Tukol_and_Dr._K.K._Dixit1993">Varni, Jinendra; Ed. Prof. Sagarmal Jain, Translated Justice T.K. Tukol and Dr. K.K. Dixit (1993). <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">Samaṇ Suttaṁ</span></i>. New Delhi: Bhagwan Mahavir memorial Samiti.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%3Cspan+lang%3D%22sa-Latn%22+xml%3Alang%3D%22sa-Latn%22+title%3D%22International+Alphabet+of+Sanskrit+Transliteration%22++class%3D%22Unicode%22+style%3D%22white-space%3Anormal%3B+text-decoration%3A+none%22%3ESama%E1%B9%87+Sutta%E1%B9%81%3C%2Fspan%3E&amp;rft.aulast=Varni&amp;rft.aufirst=Jinendra&amp;rft.au=Varni%2C+Jinendra&amp;rft.au=Ed.+Prof.+Sagarmal+Jain%2C+Translated+Justice+T.K.+Tukol+and+Dr.+K.K.+Dixit&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.place=New+Delhi&amp;rft.pub=Bhagwan+Mahavir+memorial+Samiti&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ethic_of_reciprocity"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-njps-30">^ <a href="#cite_ref-njps_30-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-njps_30-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> New JPS Hebrew/English Tanakh</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGensler1996">Gensler, Harry J. (1996). <i>Formal Ethics</i>. Routledge. pp.&#160;105. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415130662" class="internal">ISBN 0415130662</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Formal+Ethics&amp;rft.aulast=Gensler&amp;rft.aufirst=Harry+J.&amp;rft.au=Gensler%2C+Harry+J.&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B105&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.isbn=0415130662&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ethic_of_reciprocity"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Talmud" title="Talmud">Talmud</a>, <i>Shabbat</i> 31a</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://marbl.library.emory.edu/DigitalExhibits/stamps/015.html" class="external text" title="http://marbl.library.emory.edu/DigitalExhibits/stamps/015.html" rel="nofollow">Sol Singer Collection of Philatelic Judaica - Emory University</a></li>
